'''Tholo Thabang Matuludi''' (born 14 January 1999) is a South African [[association football|soccer]] player who plays as a right back for [[Polokwane City F.C.|Polokwane City]] in the [[Premier Soccer League]] and the [[South Africa national soccer team|South Africa national team]].

==Career==

Playing for Polokwane City in the [[National First Division]], the team won promotion to the [[2023–24 South African Premier Division]] where Matuludi made his first-tier debut.<ref>{{soccerway|tholo-thabang-matuludi/767532}}</ref><ref name=nft/> By the 2024 winter transfer window, Matuludi had stood out as a key player for Polokwane City. Media reported interest in the player, allegedly from [[Stellenbosch FC]] and [[Cape Town City F.C. (2016)|Cape Town City]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.snl24.com/kickoff/sanews/premiership/polokwane-citys-key-player-attracts-interest-20240105|title= Polokwane City's key player attracts interest|author=Fakude, Ernest|publisher=Kick Off|date=5 January 2024|access-date=9 July 2024}}</ref> No move happened, but in the summer window, [[Orlando Pirates]] was added to the discussion.<ref name=goal>{{cite news|url=https://www.goal.com/en/lists/orlando-pirates-after-thabang-matuludi-polokwane-city-defender-reacts-to-buccaneers-transfer-rumours/bltb184c71537ed5cf6|title=Orlando Pirates after Thabang Matuludi? Polokwane City defender reacts to Buccaneers transfer rumours|author=Madyira, Michael|date=6 July 2024|publisher=Goal|access-date=9 July 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.idiskitimes.co.za/dstv-premiership/matuludi-responds-to-pirates-links/|title=Matuludi Responds To Pirates Links|date=6 July 2024|author=|publisher=iDiski Times|access-date=9 July 2024}}</ref>

==International career==

He was called up for [[South Africa national football team|South Africa]] for the [[2024 COSAFA Cup]],<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.citizen.co.za/review-online/sports-news/local-sports/2024/06/30/polokwane-city-fc-player-makes-national-squad/|title=Polokwane City FC player makes national squad|author=Rachuene, Herbert|date=30 June 2024|publisher=Polokwane Review|access-date=9 July 2024}}</ref> where he made his international debut against Mozambique.<ref name=nft>{{NFT player|95250}}</ref> He played every minute of the competition until South Africa was knocked out.<ref name=goal/>

On 1 December 2025, Matuludi was called up to the South Africa squad for the [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cafonline.com/afcon2025/news/totalenergies-afcon-morocco-2025-fever-rises-as-broos-become-first-coach-to-unveil-final-squad/|title=TotalEnergies AFCON Morocco 2025 fever rises as Broos become first coach to unveil final squad|publisher=[[Confederation of African Football]]|date=1 December 2025|access-date=12 December 2025}}</ref>

